Frequently asked questions



How can I access internet banking?

Personal, business, corporate and institutional customers can access their online accounts via our internet banking page.



I am a customer, who can I contact?


If you are a retail banking customer, the quickest route is to go to your country website using the Retail Banking and Wealth Management country selector in the grey box above. For business customers, we advise you to visit your business website or speak to your relationship manager. On these pages you will find contact details for our four global businesses and the countries in which we operate. You will also find a number of other useful links and e-mail addresses that may enable your query to be addressed quickly.  If you do not find a suitable way to contact us, please e-mail customerrelations@hsbc.com




How can I contact HSBC on social media?

HSBC is active on social media in more than 20 countries. You can find links to our channels, which include Twitter, Facebook, LinkedIn, YouTube, WeChat and Instagram, on the HSBC on social media page.



How can I find and apply for jobs at HSBC?

You can find details of career opportunities across our global network, and search and apply for jobs, on the Careers section of this website.
Visit our students and graduates page for information on programmes, placements and entry-level opportunities for people at the early stages of their career.
Read our careers frequently asked questions for more information about the application process. 



How can I contact HSBC‚Äôs press office?

Journalists can find contact details for our media relations teams in different regions around the world on our media contacts page.



Who should I contact with an investor enquiry?

Investors and analysts can read answers to common questions about shareholding, financial reporting, dividends and taxation on our frequently asked questions ‚Äì investor relations page.
If you have further questions, visit our investor contacts page to get in touch with our investor relations team.
Private shareholders can also visit the contact our registrar page to receive shareholder communications from HSBC electronically.



Where can I find more information about HSBC and its leadership, strategy, purpose and history?

Visit the About HSBC section of this website to read more about HSBC‚Äôs history and management and our objective of becoming the world‚Äôs leading international bank.  



Where can I find out more about HSBC‚Äôs approach to environmental, social and governance issues?

Visit the Our approach section of this website for information on HSBC‚Äôs values, how we do business and our commitment to diversity and inclusion.
You can find out more about HSBC‚Äôs approach to sustainability on our sustainability page.
We publish regularly updated information on our performance in relation to environmental, social and governance issues on the measuring our impact page. 



How can I find out more about HSBC's archives and contact the bank's archivists?

You can read more on our archives, and find contact details for our archivists in London, Hong Kong, New York and Paris, on the HSBC's archives page.



I have a sponsorship proposal for HSBC. What should I do?

You can find out more about HSBC‚Äôs sponsorship activities, and submit a proposal, on our sponsorship page.



I still have not found the answer to my question. What should I do?

If you are a customer and have an enquiry that has not been resolved using the contact details and information listed above, please e-mail customerrelations@hsbc.com










